# Financial Risk Credit Trade Related Contingencies Amount

## identifier
de7928

## type
float

## definition
This is the value, as at the relevant date, of any potential credit exposures arising from trade-related contingencies.
     
A trade-related contingency is a contingent (off-balance sheet) liability arising from a trade-related obligation that is secured against an underlying shipment of goods for both issuing and confirming parties. This includes but is not limited to:
     - documentary letters of credit issued;
     - acceptances on trade bills;
     - shipping guarantees issued; and
     - any other trade-related contingencies.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=FinancialRisk.Credit.TradeRelatedContingencies.Amount
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.06
- period=instant
